WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:34.520
=Lady Liberty=

00:01:35.020 --> 00:01:37.980
=Episode 33=

00:02:05.780 --> 00:02:07.700
You're here all alone, reminiscing?

00:02:35.355 --> 00:02:37.266
First time going through
something like this?

00:02:38.980 --> 00:02:40.540
It's like your first breakup

00:02:40.780 --> 00:02:42.020
or your first divorce.

00:02:43.020 --> 00:02:44.690
There's always a period like this

00:02:44.690 --> 00:02:45.930
when you can't catch your breath

00:02:45.940 --> 00:02:46.980
and your mind won't settle.

00:02:47.820 --> 00:02:48.540
That's normal.

00:02:49.620 --> 00:02:49.980
Right?

00:02:50.177 --> 00:02:52.220
Just yesterday,
this place was still full of people,

00:02:52.220 --> 00:02:53.380
busy running around here.

00:02:54.180 --> 00:02:55.180
Then, all of a sudden,

00:02:55.260 --> 00:02:56.660
it turned quiet overnight.

00:02:57.540 --> 00:02:59.220
Anyone would feel awful after that.

00:03:00.866 --> 00:03:02.720
Next time you go through
something like this,

00:03:02.740 --> 00:03:04.066
you'll feel much better about it.

00:03:05.740 --> 00:03:07.420
That's just life.

00:03:08.380 --> 00:03:10.420
Ups and downs, rises and falls.

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:12.420
No peak is impossible to reach,

00:03:12.733 --> 00:03:14.660
and no step is impossible
to come down from.

00:03:19.660 --> 00:03:20.860
I've already arranged everything

00:03:22.180 --> 00:03:23.300
for my staff and authors.

00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:27.300
There isn't any step
I must come down from.

00:03:29.780 --> 00:03:30.460
What about you?

00:03:31.660 --> 00:03:32.780
Where's your step?

00:03:53.540 --> 00:03:54.380
Zhanqiao,

00:03:56.100 --> 00:03:57.580
we're all adults.

00:03:58.340 --> 00:03:59.580
As competitors,

00:03:59.580 --> 00:04:01.140
yes, sometimes,

00:04:01.500 --> 00:04:02.900
we fight tooth and nail.

00:04:03.020 --> 00:04:03.980
But in private,

00:04:03.980 --> 00:04:06.260
there's no personal grudge between us.

00:04:06.280 --> 00:04:07.266
You admit that, don't you?

00:04:09.300 --> 00:04:11.820
I have always admired you.

00:04:12.220 --> 00:04:14.060
That's why I keep inviting you

00:04:14.060 --> 00:04:15.020
to join Dingqi.

00:04:16.380 --> 00:04:18.180
I've lost count
of how many times it's been.

00:04:19.900 --> 00:04:20.420
This time,

00:04:21.220 --> 00:04:23.780
I'm still inviting you sincerely.

00:04:25.940 --> 00:04:26.420
Don't worry.

00:04:26.620 --> 00:04:27.380
The offer

00:04:27.620 --> 00:04:29.460
will be much better than Zhao Lanxin's.

00:04:32.866 --> 00:04:34.822
Then, I'll turn you down one more time.

00:04:37.420 --> 00:04:38.380
You already have plans?

00:04:44.580 --> 00:04:45.300
Can you tell me?

00:04:48.380 --> 00:04:49.140
Not for now.

00:04:56.220 --> 00:04:57.180
You've written too much.

00:04:57.288 --> 00:04:58.260
Leave more blank space.

00:04:58.260 --> 00:04:59.700
Give them some room to imagine.

00:04:59.800 --> 00:05:00.180
Alright.

00:05:00.190 --> 00:05:01.770
Finish it first.
I'll read it after that.

00:05:01.780 --> 00:05:03.066
Alright. Go ahead and get busy.

00:05:03.422 --> 00:05:04.480
You've been waiting long?

00:05:06.260 --> 00:05:07.220
How did you know?

00:05:07.860 --> 00:05:08.780
I saw your car.

00:05:11.460 --> 00:05:12.777
The lecture was pretty good.

00:05:13.100 --> 00:05:14.260
But if you ask me,

00:05:14.260 --> 00:05:17.700
you speak less well than you write.

00:05:18.940 --> 00:05:19.780
Of course.

00:05:20.740 --> 00:05:22.020
But compared to writing novels,

00:05:22.140 --> 00:05:23.260
teaching is less stressful.

00:05:23.900 --> 00:05:25.860
And classes start
and end at fixed times.

00:05:26.266 --> 00:05:28.533
It's not as tiring
as driving for a ride-hailing service.

00:05:28.860 --> 00:05:31.180
Selling courses online
and teaching offline...

00:05:31.422 --> 00:05:32.933
How much can that really make?

00:05:34.260 --> 00:05:35.980
Much more than I need.

00:05:36.460 --> 00:05:37.020
Go ahead.

00:05:37.260 --> 00:05:38.933
What did you come all this way for?

00:05:42.620 --> 00:05:43.900
You really don't plan

00:05:44.060 --> 00:05:45.060
to write novels anymore?

00:05:45.300 --> 00:05:46.060
No.

00:05:47.460 --> 00:05:49.220
Isn't quitting
while I'm ahead a good thing?

00:05:49.220 --> 00:05:51.100
Walking away at the peak is pretty wise.

00:05:51.260 --> 00:05:53.620
If I keep writing, people
will just say I've lost my talent.

00:05:55.460 --> 00:05:57.740
Find someone to help you with it.

00:05:58.500 --> 00:05:59.660
Get another editor?

00:06:00.540 --> 00:06:01.900
Dai Shan, and Lin Zhanqiao.

00:06:02.044 --> 00:06:03.900
I've already worked
with the two best editors

00:06:03.900 --> 00:06:05.660
in the industry. Who else is there?

00:06:08.860 --> 00:06:10.140
It doesn't have to be an editor.

00:06:11.500 --> 00:06:12.100
A team?

00:06:12.980 --> 00:06:13.940
Give me a break.

00:06:14.060 --> 00:06:16.020
I write novels, not TV dramas.

00:06:20.180 --> 00:06:21.740
There are three authors here.

00:06:21.740 --> 00:06:23.620
Three different genres.

00:06:23.820 --> 00:06:24.977
Different writing styles.

00:06:25.622 --> 00:06:26.700
The newcomers you found?

00:06:32.822 --> 00:06:34.488
You didn't even write down their name.

00:06:34.620 --> 00:06:36.660
Does the secrecy really need
to be this extreme?

00:06:40.888 --> 00:06:41.580
Read them first.

00:06:41.711 --> 00:06:43.720
Call me after you finish reading,
then we'll talk.

00:06:44.140 --> 00:06:44.755
I'm leaving.

00:06:44.933 --> 00:06:45.540
Take a look.

00:06:51.540 --> 00:06:53.540
(I Sell Pancakes in a Paranormal World)

00:06:53.540 --> 00:06:55.540
(Tracing Back)

00:06:55.540 --> 00:06:57.220
(Trails of the Unorthodox)

00:07:00.860 --> 00:07:01.580
This way, ma'am.

00:07:03.420 --> 00:07:03.820
Thank you.

00:07:04.660 --> 00:07:05.500
Morning, Mr. Cai.

00:07:05.500 --> 00:07:06.266
You're here.

00:07:06.511 --> 00:07:08.100
Done handling the company's affairs?

00:07:09.180 --> 00:07:10.180
Only Zhangzhu's left.

00:07:12.620 --> 00:07:13.380
I'm sorry.

00:07:13.980 --> 00:07:16.100
I couldn't give Zhangzhu
a better future.

00:07:16.900 --> 00:07:17.460
It's alright.

00:07:17.866 --> 00:07:19.888
Did you know Zhangzhu
wants to be a writer?

00:07:20.355 --> 00:07:21.620
I'm just a labor contractor.

00:07:21.620 --> 00:07:23.360
If my daughter's dream
is to become a writer,

00:07:23.377 --> 00:07:24.880
what future could be better than that?

00:07:26.020 --> 00:07:27.200
Come on, have a look around.

00:07:31.820 --> 00:07:32.820
This place

00:07:33.500 --> 00:07:34.820
is a little too expensive for me.

00:07:35.700 --> 00:07:36.660
Just take a look around.

00:07:37.660 --> 00:07:39.020
At this stage, I think

00:07:39.222 --> 00:07:40.844
it's better to look without buying.

00:07:40.850 --> 00:07:41.860
When you're at a low point,

00:07:41.860 --> 00:07:43.130
I wouldn't recommend buying a house.

00:07:43.140 --> 00:07:44.620
But you can still look around more.

00:07:44.622 --> 00:07:46.088
See what kind of place you want.

00:07:46.333 --> 00:07:47.820
Because the kind of house you choose

00:07:47.955 --> 00:07:50.022
is the kind of life
you'll have in the future.

00:07:50.580 --> 00:07:52.260
For now, just rent a place

00:07:52.660 --> 00:07:53.860
or stay in a hotel for a while.

00:07:54.860 --> 00:07:56.700
Tell yourself it's only temporary.

00:07:57.466 --> 00:07:58.420
It'll pass eventually.

00:08:01.420 --> 00:08:02.060
Thank you.

00:08:02.688 --> 00:08:05.155
Taking time out
of your busy schedule to comfort me.

00:08:06.980 --> 00:08:08.820
Everyone goes through rough patches.

00:08:09.500 --> 00:08:11.820
Using our resources
to support each other a little

00:08:11.820 --> 00:08:13.044
is a pretty good tradition.

00:08:13.500 --> 00:08:14.660
Let me say this again.

00:08:15.140 --> 00:08:16.860
People are social creatures.

00:08:17.860 --> 00:08:19.220
We need to talk to each other,

00:08:19.300 --> 00:08:20.180
need each other,

00:08:20.580 --> 00:08:21.500
and rely on each other.

00:08:22.377 --> 00:08:23.533
I don't agree with

00:08:23.540 --> 00:08:26.080
always talking about independence,
taking everything on yourself,

00:08:26.180 --> 00:08:27.300
and handling it all alone.

00:08:29.260 --> 00:08:30.500
Call me when you have time.

00:08:30.700 --> 00:08:32.377
I'll show you
some other developments too.

00:08:32.422 --> 00:08:34.444
So you can picture yourself
in a different future.

00:08:34.740 --> 00:08:35.340
Who knows,

00:08:35.620 --> 00:08:38.220
you might be moved by one of them?

00:08:45.100 --> 00:08:46.980
Was that a property sales pitch?

00:08:49.420 --> 00:08:50.660
Not just for selling property.

00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:52.420
If,

00:08:53.380 --> 00:08:54.460
and I mean if,

00:08:55.260 --> 00:08:56.900
I could be part of your future,

00:08:58.020 --> 00:08:59.260
I'd be more than happy to.

00:09:01.940 --> 00:09:02.740
Also,

00:09:03.660 --> 00:09:05.620
no matter what the situation is,

00:09:06.420 --> 00:09:07.660
I can handle it.

00:09:11.500 --> 00:09:12.620
But don't feel pressured.

00:09:13.100 --> 00:09:14.500
I'm just giving you another option.

00:09:16.180 --> 00:09:16.700
Thank you.

00:09:17.740 --> 00:09:18.700
But I probably

00:09:19.580 --> 00:09:20.700
won't choose that option.

00:09:24.660 --> 00:09:25.020
Alright.

00:09:25.460 --> 00:09:26.340
That's okay.

00:09:27.540 --> 00:09:29.020
But no matter what,

00:09:29.020 --> 00:09:31.180
He Han can't be your only option, right?

00:09:33.820 --> 00:09:35.380
That doesn't really count as an option.

00:09:36.500 --> 00:09:37.380
More like a footnote.

00:09:39.140 --> 00:09:40.500
Under my profile,

00:09:40.844 --> 00:09:42.755
there were never
any options to begin with.

00:09:54.844 --> 00:09:55.820
Zhou Mei, you're here.

00:09:56.460 --> 00:09:56.780
Come.

00:09:57.200 --> 00:09:58.288
I'll sit here instead.

00:10:01.580 --> 00:10:02.980
What would you like to drink?

00:10:04.900 --> 00:10:05.340
No need.

00:10:09.777 --> 00:10:11.466
Where are my mom and her lawyer?

00:10:13.300 --> 00:10:15.180
I've been calling her the whole time,

00:10:15.180 --> 00:10:16.140
but she won't answer.

00:10:23.700 --> 00:10:24.100
Zhou Mei.

00:10:25.355 --> 00:10:26.100
Hello, Mr. Zhou.

00:10:27.260 --> 00:10:28.180
Hello.

00:10:31.700 --> 00:10:33.500
Don't tell me you're the lawyer
my mom hired?

00:10:35.844 --> 00:10:36.644
Where is she?

00:10:37.060 --> 00:10:37.900
She left Shanghai.

00:10:38.800 --> 00:10:40.844
She asked me to handle
the house matter for her.

00:10:40.980 --> 00:10:42.580
Although this isn't my specialty,

00:10:42.820 --> 00:10:44.460
she asked me for help,

00:10:44.580 --> 00:10:45.533
and I was glad to help.

00:10:45.660 --> 00:10:46.733
It's no trouble at all.

00:10:48.340 --> 00:10:49.060
She contacted you?

00:10:49.866 --> 00:10:51.650
I've always kept in touch
with your mother.

00:10:52.133 --> 00:10:53.555
Zhou Mei's mother agreed

00:10:53.622 --> 00:10:55.820
to split the house payment
equally with you, Mr. Zhou.

00:10:59.660 --> 00:11:00.380
It's that simple?

00:11:02.900 --> 00:11:04.820
That was my condition from the start.

00:11:05.500 --> 00:11:06.100
But her?

00:11:08.900 --> 00:11:09.580
For 20 years,

00:11:10.380 --> 00:11:11.460
she refused to budge.

00:11:12.460 --> 00:11:14.180
She had her reasons for not giving in.

00:11:14.777 --> 00:11:16.355
She thought if she kept the house,

00:11:16.511 --> 00:11:18.133
you'd still come back and live there.

00:11:18.222 --> 00:11:19.900
Now she doesn't have
that concern anymore.

00:11:20.111 --> 00:11:21.666
So, there isn't a problem anymore.

00:11:21.933 --> 00:11:23.460
If neither of you has any objections,

00:11:23.500 --> 00:11:25.155
I'll help handle the contract afterward.

00:11:25.422 --> 00:11:26.666
I don't have any objections.

00:11:26.733 --> 00:11:27.666
The sooner, the better.

00:11:27.780 --> 00:11:29.860
Hopefully, I can get
the money this month,

00:11:30.466 --> 00:11:31.340
so I'll still have time

00:11:31.420 --> 00:11:32.580
to invest in a new project.

00:11:33.660 --> 00:11:33.980
Dad.

00:11:37.500 --> 00:11:37.900
Zhou Mei,

00:11:38.860 --> 00:11:40.100
I know what you're going to say.

00:11:41.100 --> 00:11:43.140
But I'm just a businessman.

00:11:43.740 --> 00:11:46.260
I never really cared about living out
my later years in comfort.

00:11:47.820 --> 00:11:48.700
The only thing I enjoy

00:11:48.980 --> 00:11:49.860
is doing business.

00:11:51.980 --> 00:11:53.180
If a deal fails,

00:11:53.422 --> 00:11:54.533
I'll accept it.

00:11:55.380 --> 00:11:55.940
But...

00:11:56.740 --> 00:11:57.900
as long as I still have money,

00:11:58.340 --> 00:11:59.460
I'll keep taking my shot.

00:12:11.377 --> 00:12:12.222
Alright then.

00:12:18.180 --> 00:12:18.940
You can stay

00:12:19.577 --> 00:12:21.711
at my house
until the payment comes through.

00:12:28.660 --> 00:12:29.140
Thank you.

00:12:38.333 --> 00:12:39.911
It's been a long time since we last met.

00:12:41.060 --> 00:12:41.500
Yeah.

00:12:42.355 --> 00:12:43.580
How's the new law firm?

00:12:44.460 --> 00:12:44.980
Really good.

00:12:45.088 --> 00:12:46.460
The more industries transform,

00:12:46.460 --> 00:12:47.622
the better business gets for us.

00:12:47.900 --> 00:12:50.020
And now, I'm making a lot of money.

00:12:52.022 --> 00:12:53.580
I can tell just by looking at you.

00:12:54.733 --> 00:12:56.355
Heading to the office? I'll drive you.

00:12:56.740 --> 00:12:57.060
Sure.

00:12:59.020 --> 00:13:00.460
Let me move my things so you can sit.

00:13:01.500 --> 00:13:02.220
Got a new car?

00:13:06.420 --> 00:13:07.420
This car of yours

00:13:07.700 --> 00:13:09.140
is already better than Lawyer Bei's.

00:13:09.733 --> 00:13:11.288
Things really have changed a lot.

00:13:13.500 --> 00:13:13.860
Yeah.

00:13:15.100 --> 00:13:16.860
I used to think
becoming someone important

00:13:17.488 --> 00:13:19.066
was like climbing a mountain,

00:13:19.180 --> 00:13:20.740
slowly making your way up step by step.

00:13:20.866 --> 00:13:23.200
Your salary goes from
a few thousand to tens of thousands.

00:13:23.622 --> 00:13:25.888
But later I realized
that once you get an opportunity,

00:13:26.020 --> 00:13:28.180
your income
starts growing exponentially.

00:13:28.466 --> 00:13:30.490
From tens of thousands
to hundreds of thousands,

00:13:30.490 --> 00:13:32.100
millions, even tens of millions.

00:13:33.377 --> 00:13:35.066
Of course, I haven't gotten there yet.

00:13:35.660 --> 00:13:37.700
But I've already figured out the trick.

00:13:48.660 --> 00:13:50.100
For a very long time,

00:13:51.100 --> 00:13:53.780
the mentor and his wife seemed like
they still hadn't processed it.

00:13:55.140 --> 00:13:56.820
As if nothing had happened

00:13:56.820 --> 00:13:58.260
to the family at all.

00:13:58.577 --> 00:14:00.066
Everything stayed the same as always.

00:14:02.300 --> 00:14:03.260
Until the day Bu Xi

00:14:04.140 --> 00:14:05.700
left the Yan family,

00:14:07.980 --> 00:14:09.500
she deliberately chose

00:14:11.060 --> 00:14:12.700
a drizzly evening

00:14:16.500 --> 00:14:18.940
because there were fewer people around.

00:14:20.780 --> 00:14:23.140
The Su family sent a sedan

00:14:24.380 --> 00:14:25.300
to pick Bu Xi up.

00:14:27.100 --> 00:14:28.780
Only her mother was in the car.

00:14:30.060 --> 00:14:31.420
Though she looked worn with worry,

00:14:32.500 --> 00:14:34.300
you could still sense

00:14:34.780 --> 00:14:35.620
her composure

00:14:36.500 --> 00:14:37.340
and restraint.

00:14:45.780 --> 00:14:46.740
What are you reading?

00:14:47.860 --> 00:14:49.820
A new book by the Guangzhou
writer Zhang Xin.

00:14:51.300 --> 00:14:52.500
The author of Foxtrot Murder?

00:14:55.300 --> 00:14:56.140
My mom used to

00:14:56.420 --> 00:14:58.500
watch TV adaptations
of her novels all the time.

00:15:09.733 --> 00:15:12.320
You said on the phone she
wouldn't be doing the surgery anymore.

00:15:13.300 --> 00:15:14.060
What do you mean?

00:15:15.400 --> 00:15:16.940
The doctor came to see me this morning.

00:15:17.020 --> 00:15:18.420
He asked me to discuss with you

00:15:18.620 --> 00:15:20.177
whether we should consider surgery.

00:15:21.860 --> 00:15:23.820
The success rate
of this surgery isn't very high.

00:15:25.020 --> 00:15:26.180
But if we don't do it,

00:15:27.533 --> 00:15:29.180
the gastric lymphoma has already spread.

00:15:29.860 --> 00:15:30.580
The doctor said

00:15:31.660 --> 00:15:32.700
anytime she would...

00:15:32.955 --> 00:15:34.688
What are we supposed to do now?

00:15:36.500 --> 00:15:37.220
The doctor said

00:15:37.980 --> 00:15:40.060
there are very limited
treatment options left.

00:15:41.540 --> 00:15:43.220
A lot of the treatments
your mother needs,

00:15:43.460 --> 00:15:44.933
her body can no longer handle.

00:15:51.955 --> 00:15:53.460
I need to ask around again myself.

00:15:55.140 --> 00:15:56.060
I'll ask them

00:15:56.222 --> 00:15:58.377
if there are
any similar cases before this.

00:15:59.600 --> 00:16:00.500
The odds aren't high.

00:16:00.900 --> 00:16:02.100
But exactly how low are they?

00:16:02.933 --> 00:16:04.466
I already told the doctor

00:16:05.044 --> 00:16:06.688
we're not doing the surgery anymore.

00:16:08.780 --> 00:16:09.300
Why?

00:16:10.488 --> 00:16:12.740
Didn't the doctor say
you should discuss it with me?

00:16:12.740 --> 00:16:14.020
You never discussed it with me.

00:16:15.888 --> 00:16:16.940
Your mother once told me

00:16:19.060 --> 00:16:20.820
that if she could still move and speak,

00:16:21.222 --> 00:16:24.066
whether to undergo surgery
or intubation would be her own decision.

00:16:25.466 --> 00:16:27.260
But if she could no longer
move or speak,

00:16:28.340 --> 00:16:29.420
her decision would be

00:16:30.580 --> 00:16:31.980
not to do surgery or intubation.

00:16:36.780 --> 00:16:38.420
I still need to ask around again myself.

00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:40.450
Let's talk after I get a clear answer.

00:16:40.460 --> 00:16:41.020
Stop asking.

00:16:41.377 --> 00:16:42.930
The more you ask,
the more you will hesitate,

00:16:42.930 --> 00:16:44.290
and it'll make the decision even harder.

00:16:44.300 --> 00:16:45.060
But what if?

00:16:45.260 --> 00:16:46.577
What if there's still a chance?

00:16:51.740 --> 00:16:52.820
At my age,

00:16:54.140 --> 00:16:56.580
if the person lying here
right now were me,

00:16:57.780 --> 00:16:59.060
I think I would make

00:16:59.060 --> 00:17:00.340
the same decision as your mother.

00:17:00.422 --> 00:17:01.500
Yes, you think you would,

00:17:01.500 --> 00:17:03.100
but that's only your own perspective.

00:17:03.955 --> 00:17:06.180
Aren't you projecting
your own feelings onto her?

00:17:07.060 --> 00:17:08.540
But who doesn't do that?

00:17:13.180 --> 00:17:13.980
So now,

00:17:15.020 --> 00:17:16.620
we just sit here and watch her leave?

00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:46.820
Don't be too upset.

00:17:49.060 --> 00:17:49.940
As parents,

00:17:51.180 --> 00:17:52.260
no matter when,

00:17:52.822 --> 00:17:55.180
we never want our children
to be upset because of us.

00:17:57.488 --> 00:17:59.400
We only hope
they can live easily and happily.

00:18:13.700 --> 00:18:14.860
As for this matter,

00:18:15.780 --> 00:18:18.060
the first reaction of her father,
Su Dakuo, was fury.

00:18:19.620 --> 00:18:20.460
After calming down,

00:18:20.622 --> 00:18:22.780
he wanted Bu Xi
to remain with the Yan family

00:18:23.780 --> 00:18:24.620
and tell everyone

00:18:25.111 --> 00:18:26.980
that Yan Zheng
had gone away to study again.

00:18:28.460 --> 00:18:30.300
At least this way, they could save face.

00:18:32.400 --> 00:18:34.660
For once, her mother
threatened him with her life.

00:18:35.620 --> 00:18:36.100
She said,

00:18:36.540 --> 00:18:38.140
Bu Xi is only 22 years old.

00:18:38.777 --> 00:18:41.155
How is she supposed
to live the rest of her life?

00:18:41.740 --> 00:18:42.940
Is men's pride

00:18:43.500 --> 00:18:45.540
really worth ruining
their daughter's entire life?

00:18:47.100 --> 00:18:48.580
I am taking my daughter home with me.

00:18:50.540 --> 00:18:51.860
You can divorce me if you want.

00:18:53.060 --> 00:18:54.900
I'll take my daughter
back to my family home.

00:18:55.977 --> 00:18:57.333
My father isn't like you.

00:18:57.577 --> 00:18:59.220
He would feel sorry for his daughter.

00:19:00.820 --> 00:19:02.620
When I got married, my father told me,

00:19:03.900 --> 00:19:05.940
"There's a rice shop under your name.

00:19:07.300 --> 00:19:09.140
If Su Dakuo ever mistreats you,

00:19:10.022 --> 00:19:11.060
come home immediately.

00:19:11.644 --> 00:19:13.820
Your maiden family
is your last source of support."

00:19:49.244 --> 00:19:50.577
I've finished reading them.

00:19:51.140 --> 00:19:52.220
All three were pretty good.

00:19:52.311 --> 00:19:54.155
Not just pretty good,
but they were excellent.

00:19:54.220 --> 00:19:56.222
Don't tell me who wrote them yet.
Let me guess.

00:19:56.288 --> 00:19:57.700
One of them should be
by a new writer, right?

00:19:57.700 --> 00:19:58.580
The other two aren't.

00:19:58.980 --> 00:19:59.866
The one... Trails?

00:19:59.911 --> 00:20:01.780
Even though it's a male-oriented story,

00:20:01.780 --> 00:20:03.180
the author should be a woman, right?

00:20:03.940 --> 00:20:04.740
And the last one,

00:20:05.580 --> 00:20:06.380
Tracing Back.

00:20:08.333 --> 00:20:09.340
I think out of the three,

00:20:09.340 --> 00:20:10.577
that's the best-written one.

00:20:10.700 --> 00:20:12.333
They wouldn't even need to work with me.

00:20:12.400 --> 00:20:13.990
They could climb
the rankings on their own.

00:20:14.100 --> 00:20:16.000
There's more than just three.
There's more.

00:20:16.555 --> 00:20:18.133
There's more than just these three?

00:20:18.155 --> 00:20:19.800
How many more do you have?

00:20:20.380 --> 00:20:21.460
As many as you want.

00:20:57.900 --> 00:21:00.180
(Zhanqiao)

00:21:14.500 --> 00:21:14.860
Hello?

00:21:16.460 --> 00:21:18.540
Your friend drank quite a lot over here.

00:22:02.177 --> 00:22:03.200
You're here.

00:22:03.844 --> 00:22:05.400
Now you're the one not drinking,

00:22:06.155 --> 00:22:08.000
and she's started drinking instead.

00:22:14.666 --> 00:22:15.860
What's wrong with you?

00:22:15.940 --> 00:22:17.140
Why are you drinking here?

00:22:19.300 --> 00:22:20.660
I used to have work the next day,

00:22:20.660 --> 00:22:21.740
so I didn't dare drink.

00:22:22.000 --> 00:22:24.200
I was afraid I wouldn't
get up the next morning.

00:22:25.180 --> 00:22:25.940
But now,

00:22:26.088 --> 00:22:27.900
there's nothing left
to keep me busy anyway.

00:22:28.577 --> 00:22:29.860
So I figured I'd drink a little

00:22:29.860 --> 00:22:30.820
to help me sleep.

00:22:34.740 --> 00:22:36.460
Alcohol really is a strange thing.

00:22:38.180 --> 00:22:39.660
Some people never drink,

00:22:40.022 --> 00:22:41.377
and suddenly one day,

00:22:41.940 --> 00:22:43.100
they start drinking.

00:22:43.980 --> 00:22:44.410
Thanks.

00:22:44.410 --> 00:22:45.660
And some people always drink,

00:22:45.888 --> 00:22:47.620
and suddenly one day,
they stop drinking.

00:22:49.420 --> 00:22:51.020
That's why everyone's turning point

00:22:51.340 --> 00:22:51.940
is different.

00:22:53.733 --> 00:22:54.780
I really don't get it.

00:23:00.620 --> 00:23:01.820
Who are you replying to?

00:23:01.940 --> 00:23:03.911
The company's gone.
Who are you even emailing?

00:23:04.500 --> 00:23:05.420
My lawyer.

00:23:06.220 --> 00:23:06.900
What lawyer?

00:23:10.020 --> 00:23:11.420
Even though Chenxing has shut down,

00:23:11.420 --> 00:23:12.100
it still

00:23:13.020 --> 00:23:14.100
hasn't officially dissolved.

00:23:15.022 --> 00:23:17.222
So technically,
I still have some money coming in.

00:23:18.533 --> 00:23:20.380
It's Gu Yan's breach
of contract payment.

00:23:21.500 --> 00:23:22.500
But right now,

00:23:23.180 --> 00:23:24.820
the lawsuit still isn't over,

00:23:24.820 --> 00:23:25.420
so...

00:23:26.340 --> 00:23:27.820
I haven't received the money yet.

00:23:31.222 --> 00:23:33.177
What are you planning
to do once you get it?

00:23:37.220 --> 00:23:38.340
Probably two options.

00:23:40.140 --> 00:23:40.540
First,

00:23:41.311 --> 00:23:42.340
start all over again.

00:23:43.380 --> 00:23:45.340
Get back up where I fell.

00:23:46.777 --> 00:23:48.700
After all, I've already
gone through one failure.

00:23:48.700 --> 00:23:49.340
So,

00:23:51.260 --> 00:23:53.140
I should do better
the second time around.

00:23:57.820 --> 00:23:58.820
And the other option?

00:24:01.980 --> 00:24:04.540
These past few years,
overseas online fiction

00:24:04.933 --> 00:24:06.444
has been growing incredibly fast.

00:24:06.540 --> 00:24:08.355
But it still
hasn't reached a real scale,

00:24:09.860 --> 00:24:11.540
and when it comes to developing writers,

00:24:11.711 --> 00:24:13.333
it's always lagging behind.

00:24:15.140 --> 00:24:17.300
So actually, Ma and I
have already been in touch.

00:24:18.580 --> 00:24:19.820
He's been working in this field

00:24:21.460 --> 00:24:23.060
for many years already.

00:24:30.644 --> 00:24:32.177
You're going to Los Angeles?

00:24:34.800 --> 00:24:36.140
You could say that's one option.

00:24:38.340 --> 00:24:39.220
But the prerequisite

00:24:40.688 --> 00:24:43.111
is that I need to settle things
for my parents first.

00:25:13.060 --> 00:25:14.580
If you were to rebuild Chenxing,

00:25:16.888 --> 00:25:19.000
would you still do things
the same way as before,

00:25:19.088 --> 00:25:20.980
finding writers
and developing content yourself?

00:25:23.800 --> 00:25:25.900
I think there'd
be a bit more flexibility now.

00:25:27.777 --> 00:25:29.577
(There's more than just these three?)

00:25:29.600 --> 00:25:31.111
(How many more do you have?)

00:25:31.580 --> 00:25:32.620
As many as you want.

00:25:33.644 --> 00:25:34.755
Wait, what do you mean?

00:25:35.422 --> 00:25:37.060
Where are you finding so many people?

00:25:37.155 --> 00:25:38.140
They're not people.

00:25:38.911 --> 00:25:40.020
They're written by AI.

00:25:42.580 --> 00:25:43.780
Give it one idea,

00:25:43.780 --> 00:25:46.340
and within ten minutes,
it'll give you ten settings.

00:25:46.860 --> 00:25:48.060
Give it one setting,

00:25:48.140 --> 00:25:49.100
and within half an hour,

00:25:49.380 --> 00:25:50.700
it'll produce an outline for you.

00:25:51.733 --> 00:25:53.380
Who can outwrite something like that?

00:25:54.180 --> 00:25:54.700
(So?)

00:25:55.180 --> 00:25:57.140
(The assistant I found
for you isn't bad, right?)

00:26:11.700 --> 00:26:12.860
If I invited you

00:26:13.980 --> 00:26:15.220
to start over with me,

00:26:16.340 --> 00:26:16.980
would you come?

00:26:24.860 --> 00:26:25.540
No.

00:26:27.288 --> 00:26:28.820
And I think you should stop too.

00:26:29.444 --> 00:26:31.460
If you go overseas
and expand the market now,

00:26:31.460 --> 00:26:33.088
you'll probably
have a better future there.

00:26:42.577 --> 00:26:43.780
Why are you laughing?

00:26:51.660 --> 00:26:52.700
I'm laughing at myself.

00:27:10.220 --> 00:27:11.500
She gave you two choices

00:27:11.888 --> 00:27:13.711
because she wanted you to choose her.

00:27:14.860 --> 00:27:16.500
You should understand that, right?

00:27:18.260 --> 00:27:18.660
Alright.

00:27:18.777 --> 00:27:20.380
You really hurt her feelings this time.

00:27:20.380 --> 00:27:21.977
I was doing it for her own good.

00:27:22.177 --> 00:27:24.800
She's a grown woman. She doesn't
need you deciding what's best for her.

00:27:25.540 --> 00:27:26.220
I'm telling you,

00:27:26.422 --> 00:27:27.288
when she said

00:27:27.660 --> 00:27:29.020
starting the company over again,

00:27:29.340 --> 00:27:30.380
that part was fake.

00:27:31.780 --> 00:27:32.980
Starting over with you

00:27:34.860 --> 00:27:36.100
was the real part.

00:27:36.800 --> 00:27:37.460
Alright then.

00:27:37.688 --> 00:27:39.020
You've rejected her this time.

00:27:40.020 --> 00:27:40.860
You really

00:27:41.300 --> 00:27:41.740
are...

00:27:47.180 --> 00:27:50.940
(I Sell Pancakes in a Paranormal World.
I. World-building)

00:27:50.940 --> 00:27:53.180
(Trails of the Unorthodox
I. World-building and Story Background)

00:27:57.180 --> 00:28:02.300
(Shanghai Lingqi Entertainment
Information Technology Co., Ltd.)

00:28:05.620 --> 00:28:06.980
I've never heard

00:28:07.060 --> 00:28:08.444
of the company you mentioned.

00:28:09.900 --> 00:28:10.820
That doesn't matter.

00:28:10.980 --> 00:28:12.600
You'll know about it soon enough.

00:28:13.820 --> 00:28:15.100
Of course I'm one of the people

00:28:15.220 --> 00:28:16.844
who least want this industry to change.

00:28:17.066 --> 00:28:19.422
After all, I haven't enjoyed
this room enough yet.

00:28:21.866 --> 00:28:22.933
I almost forgot.

00:28:23.340 --> 00:28:25.500
This room should
feel familiar to you, right?

00:28:27.980 --> 00:28:29.860
The people who sit in this room

00:28:29.860 --> 00:28:32.460
always get the news first.

00:28:32.580 --> 00:28:34.311
They turn around
before anyone else does.

00:28:34.420 --> 00:28:36.220
The people who get the information first

00:28:36.420 --> 00:28:38.180
are the ones who stay unbeatable.

00:28:41.060 --> 00:28:42.100
Have you met Mr. Fan yet?

00:28:42.660 --> 00:28:43.740
He'll come see me.

00:28:47.300 --> 00:28:48.260
All I can say is

00:28:48.533 --> 00:28:51.288
I'll keep an eye on the information
you mentioned today.

00:28:54.333 --> 00:28:55.822
Stay in touch with me anytime.

00:28:56.620 --> 00:28:57.900
A wise man

00:28:58.577 --> 00:28:59.660
knows when to adapt.

00:29:08.066 --> 00:29:08.977
By the way,

00:29:09.220 --> 00:29:10.220
I should thank you too,

00:29:10.380 --> 00:29:13.020
for making time to see me this late.

00:29:15.377 --> 00:29:17.044
I arranged to meet you at this hour

00:29:17.066 --> 00:29:19.444
because I didn't want the others
at the company seeing us.

00:29:20.533 --> 00:29:21.311
I understand.

00:29:21.888 --> 00:29:23.155
I'm leaving.

00:29:39.420 --> 00:29:41.020
(Trails of the Unorthodox)

00:29:41.020 --> 00:29:42.620
(Tracing Back)

00:29:42.620 --> 00:29:43.980
(I Sell Pancakes in a Paranormal World)

00:30:05.822 --> 00:30:06.740
You're back so late.

00:30:06.840 --> 00:30:07.955
Did you go to the hospital?

00:30:13.540 --> 00:30:13.860
Mei,

00:30:15.444 --> 00:30:16.711
I probably can't keep living

00:30:16.800 --> 00:30:19.060
in the place Cai Dezhang rented
for us long-term anymore.

00:30:22.100 --> 00:30:22.780
I'm planning

00:30:23.260 --> 00:30:24.260
to leave Shanghai.

00:30:34.500 --> 00:30:35.500
You went to see He Han?

00:30:39.420 --> 00:30:40.100
What did he say?

00:30:43.533 --> 00:30:44.460
He didn't plan on

00:30:44.555 --> 00:30:46.711
getting back together with me.

00:31:11.140 --> 00:31:12.300
So, you're saying

00:31:13.860 --> 00:31:14.820
you told him

00:31:14.940 --> 00:31:17.088
you wanted to start over
and he turned you down?

00:31:19.700 --> 00:31:20.660
Did he say why?

00:31:24.580 --> 00:31:25.220
No future.

00:31:26.900 --> 00:31:27.580
No prospects.

00:31:40.380 --> 00:31:41.380
I used to think

00:31:42.780 --> 00:31:44.060
he just wasn't very good

00:31:44.060 --> 00:31:45.460
at expressing his feelings.

00:31:45.688 --> 00:31:47.140
I thought he was
giving up on himself

00:31:47.140 --> 00:31:48.977
while waiting for you to go back to him.

00:31:49.860 --> 00:31:50.660
I didn't expect...

00:31:51.620 --> 00:31:52.220
I was the one

00:31:52.511 --> 00:31:53.940
being sentimental all by myself.

00:32:02.500 --> 00:32:03.660
So now I...

00:32:04.700 --> 00:32:05.460
I'm planning

00:32:06.200 --> 00:32:08.400
to find a hotel near my mom's hospital

00:32:08.900 --> 00:32:10.180
and stay there for now.

00:32:16.340 --> 00:32:17.300
I can go back home.

00:32:17.533 --> 00:32:19.088
You don't need to worry about me.

00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:23.220
My dad will move out
once he gets the housing payment.

00:32:26.644 --> 00:32:27.977
Have you seen your mom yet?

00:32:28.580 --> 00:32:28.940
No.

00:32:37.340 --> 00:32:39.420
So only Zhang Yousen knows
where your mom lives?

00:32:44.140 --> 00:32:44.820
In Guizhou.

00:32:47.300 --> 00:32:49.260
But he didn't tell me
the exact location.

00:33:03.020 --> 00:33:04.060
Who would've thought

00:33:07.800 --> 00:33:09.555
that with technology this advanced,

00:33:11.300 --> 00:33:12.020
we would be

00:33:13.020 --> 00:33:15.020
daughters who can't even
reach our own mothers?

00:33:37.500 --> 00:33:38.820
If you move abroad,

00:33:40.311 --> 00:33:41.644
will your dad go with you?

00:33:45.133 --> 00:33:46.555
I want to bring him with me.

00:33:48.700 --> 00:33:49.700
I just hope he'll agree.

00:33:54.740 --> 00:33:55.980
If he doesn't,

00:33:58.222 --> 00:33:59.260
I can take care of him.

00:34:17.940 --> 00:34:18.980
She suddenly remembered

00:34:19.180 --> 00:34:20.900
that soul-shaking dinner

00:34:21.540 --> 00:34:23.380
at Yuxian Pavilion.

00:34:24.980 --> 00:34:27.660
Thankfully, the copied
ancient painting on the wall

00:34:27.660 --> 00:34:28.980
softened the tension.

00:34:30.380 --> 00:34:31.620
Sometimes, elegance

00:34:32.420 --> 00:34:34.700
only needs the slightest touch.

00:34:36.133 --> 00:34:37.940
Xinjiao slowly spread out
her brush and ink

00:34:37.940 --> 00:34:40.260
and copied down a poem by Sun Guangxian,

00:34:40.940 --> 00:34:41.980
Shangxing Cup.

00:34:44.100 --> 00:34:46.700
Silken robes in sorrow,
the pipes and strings choke with grief.

00:34:47.420 --> 00:34:49.980
Parting again,
the sail's shadow fades away.

00:34:50.780 --> 00:34:52.500
River waves gleam white as snow.

00:34:54.300 --> 00:34:55.020
She thought...

00:34:55.020 --> 00:34:57.980
(Like Wind, Like Jade)

00:34:57.980 --> 00:34:59.088
this is how people...

00:35:02.140 --> 00:35:03.820
end up drifting apart...

00:35:25.420 --> 00:35:33.820
(- He Han!)
(- He Han!)

00:35:35.700 --> 00:35:37.780
(- He Han!)
(- He Han!)

00:35:39.955 --> 00:35:41.020
(Thank you, everyone.)

00:35:57.260 --> 00:36:00.220
♪My heart is beating still♪

00:36:01.340 --> 00:36:04.260
♪Sometimes I feel alone♪

00:36:05.020 --> 00:36:08.100
♪But love should not be frail♪

00:36:12.740 --> 00:36:15.740
♪Is there a spell♪

00:36:16.620 --> 00:36:19.460
♪That lies inside my head♪

00:36:19.900 --> 00:36:23.260
♪Stand naked and haunted♪

00:36:26.260 --> 00:36:27.780
♪If there's a way♪

00:36:27.780 --> 00:36:28.820
If I invited you

00:36:29.620 --> 00:36:30.860
to start over with me,

00:36:31.980 --> 00:36:32.620
would you come?

00:36:33.820 --> 00:36:34.580
♪I guess♪

00:36:34.580 --> 00:36:39.820
♪It's rising from my silence♪

00:36:41.420 --> 00:36:43.900
♪I'm nothing but the one♪

00:36:43.900 --> 00:36:48.020
♪Who paints the blue sky♪

00:36:49.100 --> 00:36:50.700
♪With all of my tears♪

00:36:50.700 --> 00:36:52.340
♪And past pain♪

00:36:52.500 --> 00:36:54.940
♪I'd still try♪

00:37:11.940 --> 00:37:12.980
You're eating way too much.

00:37:13.266 --> 00:37:14.800
Do you really need to eat this much?

00:37:14.980 --> 00:37:15.980
I have two kids.

00:37:16.140 --> 00:37:17.740
I need more high-quality protein.

00:37:18.288 --> 00:37:19.911
Milk is a high-quality protein too.

00:37:21.260 --> 00:37:22.540
So right now,

00:37:22.866 --> 00:37:25.288
this is the most important thing
to you, right?

00:37:28.820 --> 00:37:29.340
You,

00:37:29.660 --> 00:37:30.180
my children,

00:37:30.380 --> 00:37:31.860
Ling Yikai, and Colorful Culture Media

00:37:31.933 --> 00:37:33.400
are all equally important.

00:37:39.420 --> 00:37:40.580
Download this app.

00:37:43.820 --> 00:37:44.460
Lingqi?

00:37:44.460 --> 00:37:45.820
(Lingqi Reading)

00:37:46.733 --> 00:37:48.420
A new app that's gaining momentum fast.

00:37:48.533 --> 00:37:50.000
Its main focus is free reading.

00:37:50.044 --> 00:37:51.340
Mr. Fan's ex-wife started it.

00:37:52.540 --> 00:37:53.620
Is there also AI writing?

00:37:55.180 --> 00:37:55.980
I'm not sure.

00:37:56.733 --> 00:37:58.111
How do you know about it?

00:37:59.222 --> 00:37:59.980
I heard about it.

00:38:03.180 --> 00:38:04.500
I believe AI can write.

00:38:04.980 --> 00:38:05.820
But writing well?

00:38:06.666 --> 00:38:07.644
I don't buy it.

00:38:07.888 --> 00:38:09.622
A collaboration between humans and AI.

00:38:10.180 --> 00:38:11.900
Experienced writers using AI as support.

00:38:12.444 --> 00:38:13.977
That should be the idea behind it.

00:38:16.466 --> 00:38:17.900
If they poach you, will you go?

00:38:30.066 --> 00:38:31.100
Depends on the offer.

00:38:31.700 --> 00:38:32.860
Wasn't I poached by you too?

00:38:34.980 --> 00:38:36.460
You can't be that heartless.

00:38:36.622 --> 00:38:37.500
You taught me that.

00:38:41.244 --> 00:38:42.777
They already approached you?

00:38:42.980 --> 00:38:43.380
No.

00:38:55.488 --> 00:38:58.088
Good thing Zhangzhu went away
for training these few days.

00:38:58.090 --> 00:38:59.140
Otherwise, the three of us

00:38:59.140 --> 00:39:00.777
wouldn't even have a place to stay.

00:39:01.580 --> 00:39:03.370
I just want to finish moving all this

00:39:03.370 --> 00:39:04.711
before Zhangzhu comes back.

00:39:10.140 --> 00:39:11.140
If I hadn't moved,

00:39:11.140 --> 00:39:13.355
I would've never realized
I had this much stuff.

00:39:13.422 --> 00:39:15.777
Other people don't seem
to have this much stuff.

00:39:16.111 --> 00:39:17.100
Who are the other people?

00:39:17.380 --> 00:39:17.860
He Han?

00:39:20.340 --> 00:39:20.860
Yeah.

00:39:21.620 --> 00:39:22.940
Look at him moving between hotels.

00:39:23.300 --> 00:39:25.180
He just picks up
and leaves whenever he wants.

00:39:25.400 --> 00:39:27.088
He throws away
things he doesn't want anymore

00:39:27.100 --> 00:39:28.140
without hesitation.

00:39:28.780 --> 00:39:29.460
How carefree.

00:39:34.622 --> 00:39:36.180
Aren't you just moving a few boxes too?

00:39:36.980 --> 00:39:37.780
One car

00:39:37.940 --> 00:39:39.820
probably won't even fit all of my stuff.

00:39:40.540 --> 00:39:42.340
If you don't need something,
throw it away.

00:39:43.044 --> 00:39:45.466
If there's nothing you can do
about something, let it go.

00:39:45.511 --> 00:39:47.550
If there's no fate between people,
then part ways.

00:39:47.700 --> 00:39:48.660
It's all the same logic.

00:39:50.288 --> 00:39:51.444
That sounded pretty good.

00:40:36.580 --> 00:40:40.500
(Year 2015)

00:40:46.060 --> 00:40:48.420
♪If I can't have love,
then I'll choose to leave♪

00:40:48.420 --> 00:40:50.420
See, if I keep typing
with my thumb every day,

00:40:50.420 --> 00:40:51.940
will it suddenly stop working

00:40:51.940 --> 00:40:53.010
and become useless one day?

00:40:53.020 --> 00:40:56.460
♪Better to part
without winners or losers♪

00:40:56.460 --> 00:40:57.260
Probably not.

00:40:58.060 --> 00:40:59.140
But it might get bigger.

00:40:59.266 --> 00:41:00.420
Use it or lose it, right?

00:41:00.780 --> 00:41:01.340
Really?

00:41:03.644 --> 00:41:05.140
But it still seems fine right now.

00:41:05.140 --> 00:41:06.860
♪I should learn to let go♪

00:41:06.860 --> 00:41:07.900
You're so silly.

00:41:09.100 --> 00:41:10.020
"It's huge."

00:41:10.380 --> 00:41:11.740
"My thumb's huge."

00:41:15.980 --> 00:41:20.220
♪After giving everything,
I couldn't wait any longer♪

00:41:20.311 --> 00:41:22.140
(You could write on a computer.)

00:41:22.222 --> 00:41:23.822
(Everyone uses laptops to write now.)

00:41:24.020 --> 00:41:24.500
(No way.)

00:41:24.500 --> 00:41:26.650
(Laptops are heavy. You
have to carry them around every day.)

00:41:26.660 --> 00:41:29.100
(Using a phone is way more convenient.
I can pull it out and edit anytime.)

00:41:29.100 --> 00:41:30.820
♪Why bother confessing♪

00:41:31.020 --> 00:41:32.620
♪Or thinking about what to say♪

00:41:32.820 --> 00:41:35.020
♪It's none of my concern♪

00:41:35.020 --> 00:41:37.940
♪Even if it's unraveled♪

00:41:38.100 --> 00:41:39.700
♪It had fallen apart♪

00:41:39.940 --> 00:41:41.900
♪Endless dependence♪

00:41:42.100 --> 00:41:45.020
♪I really miss♪

00:41:45.180 --> 00:41:48.780
♪All the beautiful moments together♪

00:41:48.780 --> 00:41:54.220
(Phantom Knight)

00:41:54.220 --> 00:41:58.140
(Year 2014)

00:41:59.780 --> 00:42:02.980
♪Why be overly generous♪

00:42:03.180 --> 00:42:06.500
♪Beyond the limits of endurance♪

00:42:06.780 --> 00:42:10.060
♪Living in humble silence♪

00:42:10.220 --> 00:42:13.260
♪Who is it within the crowd♪

00:42:13.340 --> 00:42:16.200
(Phantom Knight)

00:42:16.660 --> 00:42:17.140
How is it?

00:42:17.260 --> 00:42:20.140
♪Who wasted their time waiting
for the wrong person♪

00:42:20.420 --> 00:42:24.100
♪In despair♪

00:42:24.340 --> 00:42:27.660
♪Saving the love you once gave me♪

00:42:27.980 --> 00:42:34.740
♪I don't need your pity♪

00:43:05.921 --> 00:43:07.041
(I've been thinking.)

00:43:08.321 --> 00:43:11.601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

00:43:12.361 --> 00:43:19.691
(is probably different.)

00:43:20.691 --> 00:43:22.441
♪If the sky♪

00:43:22.951 --> 00:43:24.351
♪And the sea♪

00:43:24.891 --> 00:43:26.601
♪Turned upside down♪

00:43:28.161 --> 00:43:30.091
♪If a swimming fish♪

00:43:30.491 --> 00:43:33.881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

00:43:35.651 --> 00:43:37.621
♪If back then♪

00:43:37.981 --> 00:43:42.391
♪We had never let go♪

00:43:42.991 --> 00:43:49.271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

00:43:50.391 --> 00:43:52.541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

00:43:52.541 --> 00:43:54.411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

00:43:54.591 --> 00:43:57.031
♪And found our way back whole♪

00:43:57.871 --> 00:44:00.041
♪So let this surging love♪

00:44:00.041 --> 00:44:04.471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

00:44:05.371 --> 00:44:07.551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

00:44:07.551 --> 00:44:08.641
♪That's alright♪

00:44:09.181 --> 00:44:09.931
♪If we're buried♪

00:44:09.931 --> 00:44:12.631
♪By passing years all the better♪

00:44:12.891 --> 00:44:15.071
♪At least we still can keep♪

00:44:15.251 --> 00:44:19.671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

00:44:35.431 --> 00:44:37.721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

00:44:37.721 --> 00:44:39.481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

00:44:39.601 --> 00:44:42.071
♪Searching all along the way♪

00:44:42.871 --> 00:44:45.031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

00:44:45.221 --> 00:44:50.131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

00:44:50.131 --> 00:44:53.651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

00:44:53.891 --> 00:44:54.861
♪Only after loss♪

00:44:54.861 --> 00:44:57.491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

00:44:57.901 --> 00:45:00.261
♪In another time and space♪

00:45:00.261 --> 00:45:01.821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

00:45:01.821 --> 00:45:04.651
♪Till we grow old♪

00:45:05.611 --> 00:45:07.901
♪But still the sky will never♪

00:45:07.901 --> 00:45:10.571
♪Turn with the sea♪

00:45:13.091 --> 00:45:15.501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

00:45:15.501 --> 00:45:20.711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪